    <div class="local-box"><p>Daylesford and Hepburn Springs sit at over 700 metres elevation in the Central Highlands — cold, misty winters with regular frosts from May through September and temperatures that genuinely demand a working fireplace. The town draws a significant proportion of Melbourne weekenders and holiday homeowners, which creates an unusual chimney sweeping challenge: fireplaces in holiday homes are used heavily during visits but often not cleaned for years on end. A fireplace that's used intensively on weekends, with whoever's visiting that particular week, and never professionally cleaned, builds up creosote faster than a regularly-used permanent home. Daylesford also has a distinctive housing stock — stone and brick heritage cottages, Arts and Crafts bungalows, timber miners' cottages — many with narrow original flues and open fireplaces that are an integral part of the property's appeal. When you rent out a Daylesford cottage or weekender with a wood fireplace, the fireplace is often the main selling point. An unserviced fireplace is both a safety risk and a liability. We're experienced with the Daylesford area, understand the holiday-home servicing dynamic, and can coordinate access around your tenancy calendar.</p></div>
